  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc6\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc8\u00a0\u0b9c\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bc8 9 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd\u00a0\u0ba8\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b95\u0ba9\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "July 9 protests demonstrate public desire to build a better Sri Lanka - Canadian Foreign Minister",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Canada's Minister of Foreign Affairs Melanie Joly has pointed out that the protests held in Sri Lanka on the 9th are a clear demonstration of the will to build a better Sri Lanka, and Canada will support constitutional measures aimed at immediate economic and political reforms.",
        "The President's House in Colombo was seized by protesters last week as popular protests that have erupted nationwide as a result of the severe economic crisis have gradually intensified.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa had announced his resignation on the 13th, but he left the country the day before yesterday.",
        "Protests against Ranil Wickramasinghe, who served as the Prime Minister, were already being carried out demanding his resignation and in the background of his house being set on fire a few days ago, the protests against him who took over as the Acting President the day before yesterday became stronger.",
        "In such a background, the Canadian Minister of Foreign Affairs, Melanie Joly, has said the above in her report on the current situation in Sri Lanka. In the post, he added:",
        "The protests that took place in Sri Lanka on the 9th are a clear indication of the great desire to build a better Sri Lanka.",
        "Accordingly, Canada will support peaceful and constitutional measures aimed at immediate economic and political reforms.",
        "At the same time, the attacks on peaceful protestors and journalists are unacceptable in any way.",
        "It is also necessary to hold accountable those involved in such violent attacks. He also emphasized that the right to carry out protests in a peaceful manner should be confirmed."
      ],
